  "prompt": "What are some good colleges in India that I can still apply to their MBA program for this year\u2019s session?",
  "response": "As of October 2023, many business schools in India may still be accepting applications for their MBA programs, depending on their specific admission cycles. Here are some well-regarded institutions that you could check for their application status:\n\n1. **Indian Institute of Management (IIM)** - Some IIMs might have late application windows or rolling admissions (like IIM Kashipur, IIM Raipur, etc.).\n   \n2. **SP Jain School of Global Management** - They often have multiple intakes throughout the year.\n\n3. **XLRI Jamshedpur** - While they primarily follow a standard admission schedule, checking for any late applications could be worthwhile.\n\n4. **Narsee Monjee Institute of Management Studies (NMIMS)** - Offers various MBA programs and may have openings depending on the specific program.\n\n5. **Symbiosis Institute of Business Management (SIBM)** - SIBM Pune often conducts multiple admission rounds.\n\n6. **Institute of Management Technology (IMT)** - IMT Ghaziabad and other campuses might have further rounds.\n\n7. **T A Pai Management Institute (TAPMI)** - Check for potential late admission notices.\n\n8. **Loyola Institute of Business Administration (LIBA)** - Known for its MBA program and sometimes has extended timelines for applications.\n\n9. **Christ University** - A private university that often has more flexible application options.\n\n10. **Bharati Vidyapeeth University** - They have several colleges with MBA programs and may still be accepting applications.\n\nIt is crucial to visit each institution's official website or contact their admissions office directly for the most current information on application deadlines and procedures, as they can vary significantly. Additionally, consider looking into state universities and lesser-known but reputable institutions as they might have different admission timelines.",
